      "content": "Here's a function that calculates the Shannon entropy for a list of IP addresses:\n\n```python\nimport math\nfrom collections import Counter\nimport itertools\n\ndef calculate_entropy(log_data):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculate the Shannon entropy of a list of IP addresses.\n\n    Args:\n    log_data (list): A list of strings representing IP addresses.\n\n    Returns:\n    float: The Shannon entropy of the IP addresses.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    # Use Counter to count the occurrences of each IP address\n    ip_counts = Counter(log_data)\n\n    # Calculate the total number of IP addresses\n    total_count = len(log_data)\n\n    # Calculate the probability of each IP address except for the most common one\n    probabilities = [(count / total_count) * math.log(count / total_count, 2) \n                     for i, (count, ip) in enumerate(ip_counts.items()) \n                     for _ in range(count)]\n\n    # Calculate the entropy by summing the probabilities\n    entropy = -sum(probabilities)\n\n    return entropy\n```\n\nThis function uses the formula for the Shannon entropy to calculate the entropy of the IP addresses. It treats each IP address as a separate probability space, and takes into account the number of times each IP address appears in the",
